def longest_substring_without_repetition(s):
    start = 1
    end = 0
    unique_chars = set()
    max_length = 0
    while end < len(s):
        if s[end] not in unique_chars:
            unique_chars.add(s[end])
            end += 1
            max_length = max(max_length, end - start)
        else:
            unique_chars.remove(s[start])
            start += 1
    return max_length
